  "prompt": "What are the home prices in Santa Clara, CA?",
  "response": "Home prices in Santa Clara, CA, are quite high and can vary significantly depending on factors like:\n\n*   **Property Type:** (Single-family home, condo, townhouse)\n*   **Size:** (Square footage, number of bedrooms/bathrooms)\n*   **Location:** (Specific neighborhood)\n*   **Condition:** (New construction, remodeled, needs work)\n*   **Market Conditions:** (Overall economic climate, interest rates, seasonality)\n\n**General Estimates (as of late 2024):**\n\n*   **Single-Family Homes:**\n    *   The median listing price for homes in Santa Clara, CA is around **$1.8 Million - $2.5 Million.** However, prices can range from **$1.3 Million** for smaller homes needing work, up to **$4 Million+** for larger, newer, or luxury properties.\n*   **Condos/Townhouses:**\n    *   Median listing prices are generally lower than single-family homes, ranging from **$700,000 to $1.2 Million.** Prices depend on size, location, and amenities.\n\n**Where to Find More Up-to-Date Information:**\n\n*   **Major Real Estate Websites:**\n    *   **Zillow:** [https://www.zillow.com/santa-clara-ca/home-values/](https://www.zillow.com/santa-clara-ca/home-values/)\n    *   **Redfin:** [https://www.redfin.com/city/17103/CA/Santa-Clara/housing-market](https://www.redfin.com/city/17103/CA/Santa-Clara/housing-market)\n    *   **Realtor.com:** [https://www.realtor.com/realestateandhomes-search/Santa-Clara_CA](https://www.realtor.com/realestateandhomes-search/Santa-Clara_CA)\n*   **Local Real Estate Agents:** A local real estate agent can provide the most accurate and up-to-date information, as they have their finger on the pulse of the local market.\n\n**Key Things to Keep in Mind:**\n\n*   **Silicon Valley Influence:** Santa Clara is in the heart of Silicon Valley, which significantly impacts housing demand and prices.\n*   **Competition:** Be prepared for a competitive market, especially for desirable properties.\n*   **Down Payment:** You'll likely need a substantial down payment.\n*   **Property Taxes:** California property taxes are subject to Proposition 13, but still factor into your overall costs.\n\nI highly recommend using the real estate websites listed above to get the most current data, and contacting a local real estate agent for personalized advice. Good luck!\n",
